Mexican Stocks: America Movil, Homex, Minera Frisco Plunge

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-05-03T21:33:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/mexican-stocks-america-movil-homex-minera-frisco-plunge.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index declined 2 percent to 35,873.21, the most
since August.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , fell 3.3 percent to 31.50
pesos. Mexico’s telecommunications regulator ruled the company
must cut by more than half the rate it charges companies
controlled by Grupo Televisa SAB to connect their calls to its
network, according to an e-mailed statement yesterday.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM) tumbled 8.2 percent to
48.15 pesos, the most since October 2009. Mexico’s largest
homebuilder reported first-quarter net income of 257 million
pesos ($22.2 million), according to a filing with Mexico’s stock
exchange yesterday. The results fell short of estimates, said
Grupo Financiero Interacciones SA analyst Marco Medina, who had
estimated profit of 316 million pesos.  Minera Frisco SAB (MFRISCOA MM) plunged 4.6 percent to
46.98 pesos, the lowest price since Jan. 13. First-quarter net
income at the mining company controlled by Slim fell 86 percent
to 51.3 million pesos ($4.4 million), according to an e-mailed
statement yesterday. Silver futures for July delivery tumbled as
much as $5.48, or 11.9 percent, to $40.60 a pound on the Comex
in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
